<inglise> COUNCIL DIRECTIVE of 20 March 1970 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to measures to be taken against air pollution by gases from positive-ignition engines of motor vehicles (70/220/EEC) </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU DIREKTIIV 70/220/EM&Uuml; mootors&otilde;idukite ottomootorite heitgaaside tekitatud &otilde;husaaste vastu v&otilde;etavaid meetmeid k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta 20. m&auml;rts 1970 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, and in particular Article 100 thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artiklit 100, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the European Parliament (1); </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the Economic and Social Committee (2); </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (2) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a regulation of 14 October 1968 amending the Stra&szlig;enverkehrs-Zulassungs-Ordnung was published in Germany in the Bundesgesetzblatt Part I of 18 October 1968; whereas that regulation contains provisions on measures to be taken against air pollution by positive-ignition engines of motor vehicles; whereas those provisions will enter into force on 1 October 1970; </inglise>
<eesti> Saksamaal avaldati 18. oktoobri 1968. aasta Bundesgesetzblatt'i I osas 14. oktoobri 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rus, millega muudetakse Sta&bgr;enverkehrs-Zulassungs-Odnung'it; k&otilde;nealune m&auml;&auml;rus sisaldab mootors&otilde;idukite ottomootorite tekitatud &otilde;husaaste vastu v&otilde;etavaid meetmeid k&auml;sitlevaid s&auml;tteid; need s&auml;tted j&otilde;ustuvad 1. oktoobril 1970; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a regulation of 31 March 1969 on the "Composition of exhaust gases emitted from petrol engines of motor vehicles" was published in France in the Journal official of 17 May 1969; whereas that regulation is applicable: </inglise>
<eesti> Prantsusmaal avaldati 17. mai 1969. aasta Journal official'is 31. m&auml;rtsi 1969. aasta m&auml;&auml;rus mootors&otilde;idukite bensiinimootorite heitgaaside koostise kohta; k&otilde;nealust m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse: </eesti>
<inglise> - from 1 September 1971, to type-approved vehicles with a new type of engine, that is to say, a type of engine which has never before been installed in a type-approved vehicle; </inglise>
<eesti> - alates 1. septembrist 1971 t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusega s&otilde;idukite suhtes, mis on varustatud uue mootorit&uuml;&uuml;biga, see t&auml;hendab sellist t&uuml;&uuml;pi mootoriga, mida ei ole varem &uuml;helegi t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusega s&otilde;idukile paigaldatud; </eesti>
<inglise> - from 1 September 1972, to vehicles put into service for the first time; </inglise>
<eesti> - alates 1. septembrist 1972 esmakordselt kasutuselev&otilde;etavate s&otilde;idukite suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas those provisions are liable to hinder the establishment and proper functioning of the common market; </inglise>
<eesti> eespool nimetatud s&auml;tted takistavad t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt &uuml;histuru loomist ja n&otilde;uetekohast toimimist; </eesti>
<inglise> whereas it is therefore necessary that all Member States adopt the same requirements, either in addition to or in place of their existing rules, in order, in particular, to allow the EEC type - approval procedure which was the subject of the Council Directive (3) of 6 February 1970 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers to be applied in respect of each type of vehicle; </inglise>
<eesti> seet&otilde;ttu on vajalik, et k&otilde;ik liikmesriigid kohaldaksid samu n&otilde;udeid, tehes olemasolevatesse eeskirjadesse lisandusi v&otilde;i asendades need uutega selleks, et eelk&otilde;ige oleks v&otilde;imalik rakendada iga s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bi puhul EM&Uuml; t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusmenetlust, mida k&auml;sitletakse n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivis mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta; (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, however, the present Directive will be applied before the date laid down for the application of the Directive of 6 February 1970; whereas at that time therefore the procedures of this last Directive will not yet be applicable; whereas therefore an ad hoc procedure must be laid down in the form of a communication certifying that a vehicle type has been tested and that it satisfies the requirements of this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevat direktiivi kohaldatakse siiski enne 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivi kohaldamise kuup&auml;eva; seet&otilde;ttu ei kohaldata veel viimati nimetatud direktiivis etten&auml;htud menetlusi; seet&otilde;ttu on tarvis ette n&auml;ha ad hoc kord teabevahetuse vormis, mis t&otilde;endab s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bi katsetamist ning vastavust k&auml;esoleva direktiivi n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, on the basis of that communication, each Member State requested to grant national type approval of a type of vehicle must be able to ascertain whether that type has been submitted to the tests laid down in this Directive; whereas, to this end, each Member State should inform the other Member States of its findings by sending them a copy of the communication completed for each type of motor vehicle which has been tested; </inglise>
<eesti> iga liikmesriik, kellelt taotletakse s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bile siseriiklikku t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust, peab k&otilde;nealusele teabevahetusele toetudes suutma kindlaks teha, kas t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse saamiseks esitatud asjaomasele s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bile on tehtud k&auml;esolevas direktiivis etten&auml;htud katsed; selleks peaks iga liikmesriik kontrollimistulemused teistele liikmesriikidele teatavaks tegema, saates nendele iga mootors&otilde;iduki t&uuml;&uuml;bi kohta teatise koopia; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas a longer period of adaptation should be laid down for industry in respect of the requirements relating to the testing of the average emission of gaseous pollutants in a congested urban area after a cold start than in respect of the other technical requirements of this Directive; </inglise>
<eesti> seoses n&otilde;uetega, mille t&auml;itmist n&otilde;utakse tihedalt asustatud linnaalal p&auml;rast k&uuml;lmk&auml;ivitust tekkivate gaasiliste heitmete keskmise heitkoguse m&auml;&auml;ramise katsetes, tuleks tootmisharule s&auml;testada pikem kohanemisaeg kui k&auml;esoleva direktiivi muude tehniliste n&otilde;uete puhul; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is desirable to use the technical requirements adopted by the UN Economic Commission for Europe in its Regulation No 15 (1) (Uniform provisions concerning the approval of vehicles equipped with a positive-ignition engine with regard to the emission of gaseous pollutants by the engine), annexed to the Agreement of 20 March 1958 concerning the adoption of uniform conditions of approval and reciprocal recognition of approval for motor vehicle equipment and parts; </inglise>
<eesti> on soovitatav arvesse v&otilde;tta tehnilisi n&otilde;udeid, mis on vastu v&otilde;etud &Uuml;RO Euroopa Majanduskomisjoni eeskirjas nr 15 (Ottomootoritega varustatud s&otilde;idukite kinnitamise &uuml;htsed s&auml;tted, milles k&auml;sitletakse mootorist v&auml;ljapaiskuvaid gaasilisi saasteaineid), (1) mis on lisatud 20. m&auml;rtsi 1958. aasta kokkuleppele mootors&otilde;idukite varustuse ja osade kinnitamise &uuml;htsete n&otilde;uete vastuv&otilde;tmise ja kinnitamise vastastikuse tunnustamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, furthermore, the technical requirements must be rapidly adapted to take account of technical progress; whereas, to this end, provision should be made for application of the procedure laid down in Article 13 of the Council Directive of 6 February 1970 on the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers; </inglise>
<eesti> peale selle tuleb tehnilisi n&otilde;udeid kiiresti kohandada tehnika arenguga; selleks tuleks s&auml;testada meetmed mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivi artiklis 13 s&auml;testatud korra kohaldamiseks, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS DIRECTIVE: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA DIREKTIIVI. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> For the purposes of this Directive, "vehicle" means any vehicle with a positive-ignition engine, intended for use on the road, with or without bodywork, having at least four wheels, a permissible maximum weight of at least 400 kg and a maximum design speed equal to or exceeding 50 km/h, with the exception of agricultural tractors and machinery and public works vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevas direktiivis t&auml;hendab "s&otilde;iduk" teedel kasutamiseks m&otilde;eldud, kerega v&otilde;i kereta, v&auml;hemalt neljarattalist, ottomootoriga varustatud mootors&otilde;idukit, mille suurim lubatud mass on v&auml;hemalt 400 kg ning valmistajakiirus on v&auml;hemalt 50 km/h, v&auml;lja arvatud p&otilde;llut&ouml;&ouml;traktorid ja -masinad ning t&ouml;&ouml;s&otilde;idukid. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> No Member State may refuse to grant EEC type approval or national type approval of a vehicle on grounds relating to air pollution by gases from positive-ignition engines of motor vehicles: </inglise>
<eesti> &Uuml;kski liikmesriik ei tohi keelduda s&otilde;idukile EM&Uuml; v&otilde;i siseriikliku t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse andmisest mootors&otilde;idukite ottomootorite heitgaasidest tuleneva &otilde;husaastega seotud p&otilde;hjustel: </eesti>
<inglise> - from 1 October 1970, where that vehicle satisfies both the requirements contained in Annex I, with the exception of those in items 3.2.1.1 and 3.2.2.1, and the requirements contained in Annexes II, IV, V and VI; </inglise>
<eesti> - alates 1. oktoobrist 1970, kui k&otilde;nealune s&otilde;iduk vastab nii I lisa n&otilde;uetele, v&auml;lja arvatud punktides 3.2.1.1 ja 3.2.2.1 etten&auml;htud n&otilde;uded, kui ka II, IV, V ja VI lisa n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise> - from 1 October 1971, where that vehicle satisfies, in addition, the requirements contained in items 3.2.1.1 and 3.2.2.1 of Annex I and in Annex III. </inglise>
<eesti> - alates 1. oktoobrist 1971, kui k&otilde;nealune s&otilde;iduk vastab lisaks ka I lisa punktide 3.2.1.1 ja 3.2.2.1 ning III lisa n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 3 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 3 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> On application being made by a manufacturer or his authorised representative, the competent authorities of the Member State concerned shall complete the sections of the communication provided for in Annex VII. </inglise>
<eesti> Asjaomase liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused t&auml;idavad tootja v&otilde;i tootja ametliku esindaja esitatud taotluse korral VII lisas etten&auml;htud teatise. </eesti>
<inglise> A copy of that communication shall be sent to the other Member States and to the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti> Teatise koopia saadetakse muudele liikmesriikidele ning taotlejale. </eesti>
<inglise> Other Member States which are requested to grant national type approval for the same type of vehicle shall accept that document as proof that the tests provided for have been carried out. </inglise>
<eesti> Muud liikmesriigid, kellelt taotletakse sama s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bi siseriiklikku t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust, aktsepteerivad saadud dokumenti etten&auml;htud katsete tegemist t&otilde;endava dokumendina. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> The provisions of paragraph 1 shall be revoked as soon as the Council Directive of 6 February 1970 on the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers enters into force. </inglise>
<eesti> L&otilde;ike 1 s&auml;tted tunnistatakse kehtetuks vahetult p&auml;rast mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivi j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 4 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 4 </eesti>
<inglise> The Member State which has granted type approval shall take the necessary measures to ensure that it is informed of any modification of a part or characteristic referred to in item 1.1 of Annex I. The competent authorities of that Member State shall determine whether fresh tests should be carried out on the modified prototype and whether a fresh report should be drawn up. </inglise>
<eesti> T&uuml;&uuml;bikinnituse andnud liikmesriik v&otilde;tab vajalikud meetmed tagamaks, et talle tehakse teatavaks mis tahes muudatused seoses I lisa punktis 1.1 nimetatud osa v&otilde;i karakteristikutega. K&otilde;nealuse liikmesriigi p&auml;devad asutused otsustavad modifitseeritud protot&uuml;&uuml;bi uue katsetamise ning uue katseprotokolli koostamise vajaduse &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise> Where such tests reveal failure to comply with the requirements of this Directive, the modification shall not be approved. </inglise>
<eesti> Kui sellisel katsetamisel ilmnevad k&otilde;rvalekalded k&auml;esoleva direktiivi n&otilde;uetest, siis muudatust ei kinnitata. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 5 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 5 </eesti>
<inglise> The amendments necessary for adjusting the requirements of Annexes I to VII so as to take account of technical progress shall be adopted in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 13 of the Council Directive of 6 February 1970 on the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers. </inglise>
<eesti> Muudatused, mis on vajalikud I ja VII lisa n&otilde;uete kohandamiseks tehnika arenguga, v&otilde;etakse vastu mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust k&auml;sitleva n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivi artiklis 13 etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 6 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 6 </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall adopt provisions containing the requirements needed in order to comply with this Directive before 30 June 1970 and shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid v&otilde;tavad enne 30. juunit 1970. aastat vastu ja avaldavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud s&auml;tted ning teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> 2. </inglise>
<eesti> 2. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall ensure that they communicate to the Commission the text of the main provisions of national law which they adopt in the field covered by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid edastavad komisjonile k&auml;esoleva direktiiviga reguleeritavas valdkonnas vastuv&otilde;etavate siseriiklike p&otilde;hiliste &otilde;igusnormide teksti. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 7 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 7 </eesti>
<inglise> This Directive is addressed to the Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev direktiiv on adresseeritud liikmesriikidele. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 20 March 1970. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 20. m&auml;rts 1970 </eesti>
